details:
Case 32 is a 42 year-old female Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to mainland China.

She reported onset of symptoms on 2 February and was admitted to Parkway East Hospital on 5 February. Subsequent test results confirmed 2019-nCoV infection on 6 February at about 11pm.

Prior to hospital admission, she worked at Victoria Junior College, but had not interacted with her colleagues and students after onset of symptoms. She stays at Elias Road and had visited Changi Airport and Singapore Zoo.
